## Best Practices

### Do

```typescript
// Use transactions for related operations
await db.transaction("rw", db.notes, db.tasks, async () => {
  // Multiple operations
});

// Use bulk operations for multiple items
await db.notes.bulkAdd(items); // Not: for-loop with add()

// Use proper indexes
this.version(1).stores({
  notes: "++id, folderId, createdAt, [folderId+createdAt]",
});

// Use useLiveQuery for reactive UI
const notes = useLiveQuery(() => db.notes.toArray());
```

### Don't

```typescript
// Don't store large blobs directly
// Use File System Access API or store reference

// Don't over-index (slows writes)
notes: "++id, *tags, title, content, createdAt, updatedAt" // Too many indexes

// Don't forget to handle errors
const notes = useLiveQuery(
  () => db.notes.toArray(),
  [],
  [] // Provide default value
);
```

